From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Real-Time Safety Co-Processor Supervisor Project <noreply@example.com>
Date: Fri, 27 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] drivers: wire in safety_copro built-in character driver

Add the Real-Time Safety Co-Processor Supervisor character driver to the
drivers tree. The driver sources live in drivers/safety_copro/ and are
copied into the kernel tree by scripts/01_build_linux_kernel.sh, so this
patch only needs to register the subdirectory with Kconfig and the build:

  - drivers/Kconfig:  add `source "drivers/safety_copro/Kconfig"`
  - drivers/Makefile: add `obj-$(CONFIG_SAFETY_COPRO) += safety_copro/`

The driver is built-in only (bool Kconfig, obj-y) and exposes
/dev/safety_copro via a misc device.

Signed-off-by: Real-Time Safety Co-Processor Supervisor Project <noreply@example.com>
---
 drivers/Kconfig  | 2 ++
 drivers/Makefile | 2 ++
 2 files changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/Kconfig b/drivers/Kconfig
index 7bdd14a7d2af..6c0d8f3b9a51 100644
--- a/drivers/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/Kconfig
@@ -243,4 +243,6 @@ source "drivers/hte/Kconfig"

 source "drivers/cdx/Kconfig"

+source "drivers/safety_copro/Kconfig"
+
 endmenu
diff --git a/drivers/Makefile b/drivers/Makefile
index 45d1c3e630f7..b9d2f3a4c1e8 100644
--- a/drivers/Makefile
+++ b/drivers/Makefile
@@ -195,3 +195,5 @@ obj-$(CONFIG_CDX_BUS)		+= cdx/
 obj-$(CONFIG_DPLL)		+= dpll/

 obj-$(CONFIG_S390)		+= s390/
+
+obj-$(CONFIG_SAFETY_COPRO)	+= safety_copro/
--
2.43.0
